   "text": "Physiology Polyuria (SIADH vs Diabetes Insipidus) diabetes-insipidus ADH water-deprivation desmopressin osmolality USMLE-style / MedKOS (renal/endocrine physiology) A 35 year old man has polyuria and polydipsia. A water deprivation test fails to concentrate his urine (urine osmolality remains low despite rising serum osmolality). After administration of desmopressin (a vasopressin analog), his urine osmolality rises by more than 50%. Which mechanism best explains his condition? A. Deficient ADH secretion from the posterior pituitary (central diabetes insipidus) B. Renal collecting duct resistance to ADH (nephrogenic diabetes insipidus) C. Excess ADH secretion (SIADH) D. Primary polydipsia with normal ADH axis E. Osmotic diuresis from glucosuria 수분제한에도 소변이 농축되지 않지만 desmopressin 투여 후 소변 삼투압이 50% 이상 증가하면 중추성 요붕증이다. ADH 분비가 부족하나 신장 반응은 정상이라 외인성 ADH에 반응한다. 신성 요붕증은 desmopressin에도 반응하지 않는다."
