   "text": "Physiology Hypoxemia (A-a Gradient) hypoxemia A-a-gradient shunt V/Q-mismatch oxygen-response USMLE-style / MedKOS (respiratory physiology) A 40 year old man with lobar pneumonia is hypoxemic. On 100% inspired oxygen his PaO2 rises only minimally, and the calculated alveolar arterial (A a) oxygen gradient is markedly elevated. Which mechanism of hypoxemia does this pattern most specifically indicate? A. Right to left shunt (perfusion of non ventilated alveoli), which does not correct with 100% oxygen B. Hypoventilation, which has a normal A a gradient C. Low inspired oxygen (high altitude), with a normal A a gradient D. Ventilation perfusion mismatch that fully corrects with 100% oxygen and has a normal A a gradient E. Impaired diffusion with a normal A a gradient A a 차이가 크면서 100% 산소로도 PaO2가 거의 오르지 않으면 우 좌 션트다. 환기되지 않는 폐포를 지나는 혈류는 산소에 노출되지 않아 보충 산소로 교정되지 않는다. 저환기·고지대는 A a가 정상이고, V/Q 부조화는 100% 산소에 대체로 교정된다."
