   "text": "Pediatrics Ductal-Dependent Cyanotic CHD cyanotic-CHD transposition PGE1 ductus-arteriosus hyperoxia-test USMLE-style / MedKOS (neonatal cardiology) A term neonate becomes profoundly cyanotic on the second day of life. The cyanosis does not improve with 100% oxygen (a failed hyperoxia test), the second heart sound is single, and a chest radiograph shows an 'egg on a string' cardiac silhouette. The infant deteriorates as the ductus arteriosus begins to close. Which of the following is the most appropriate immediate intervention? A. Start a prostaglandin E1 infusion to maintain ductal patency B. Give indomethacin to close the ductus arteriosus C. Provide high flow oxygen alone, which is sufficient D. Begin aggressive diuresis E. Start a beta blocker 산소에 반응하지 않는 신생아 청색증 + 단일 S2 + egg on a string(대혈관전위)은 관상동맥관 의존성 청색성 심질환이다. 동맥관이 닫히면 악화하므로 prostaglandin E1으로 동맥관을 열어 두는 것이 즉각적 처치다."
