   "text": "Neurology Acute Ischemic Stroke (Thrombolysis) stroke alteplase tPA 4.5-hour-window blood-pressure USMLE-style / MedKOS (AHA/ASA acute stroke guideline) A 68 year old man has sudden left hemiparesis, facial droop, and aphasia that began 2 hours ago. Blood pressure is 170/95 mmHg, fingerstick glucose is normal, and he takes no anticoagulants and has had no recent surgery or bleeding. Noncontrast head CT shows no hemorrhage and no large established infarct. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step? A. Administer intravenous alteplase now, as he is within the 4.5 hour window with no hemorrhage and no contraindication B. Give aspirin 325 mg and admit, without thrombolysis C. Rapidly lower blood pressure to below 120/80 before any therapy D. Start full dose intravenous heparin E. Withhold all treatment until MRI is obtained 발병 2시간(<4.5시간), CT에서 출혈 없음, 금기 없음, 혈압 <185/110이므로 정맥 alteplase(tPA)가 적응증이다. 급성기 과도한 혈압 강하나 즉시 헤파린은 금물이며, tPA 지연 목적의 MRI 대기도 부적절하다."
