   "snippet": "A 72 year old man has 3 weeks of low grade fever, fatigue, and weight loss. He underwent screening colonoscopy 6 weeks ago that revealed an invasive colonic adenocarcinoma. Examination reveals a new murmur of aortic regurgitation; TEE shows",
   "text": "Infectious Disease Infective Endocarditis endocarditis Enterococcus HLGR double-beta-lactam PBP USMLE-style / MedKOS (AHA/IDSA infective endocarditis guideline) A 72 year old man has 3 weeks of low grade fever, fatigue, and weight loss. He underwent screening colonoscopy 6 weeks ago that revealed an invasive colonic adenocarcinoma. Examination reveals a new murmur of aortic regurgitation; TEE shows a 9 mm aortic valve vegetation. Three sets of blood cultures grow Enterococcus faecalis that is susceptible to ampicillin and vancomycin but demonstrates high level gentamicin resistance (HLGR). Renal function is normal. Which antibiotic regimen is most appropriate? A. Ampicillin plus gentamicin B. Ampicillin plus ceftriaxone C. Vancomycin monotherapy D. Ceftriaxone monotherapy E. Daptomycin plus rifampin High level aminoglycoside 내성으로 gentamicin 상승효과를 얻을 수 없는 Enterococcus faecalis 심내막염에서는 ampicillin + ceftriaxone 이중 베타락탐이 서로 다른 PBP를 포화시켜 상승효과를 낸다. Enterococcus는 저친화도 PBP5로 cephalosporin 단독에는 내성이므로 ceftriaxone 단독은 무효."
